==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rashness
<hw>Rash"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or state of being
rash.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We offend . . . by <qex>rashness</qex>, which is an affirming or
denying, before we have sufficiently informed ourselves.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Temerity; foolhardiness; precipitancy;
precipitation; hastiness; indiscretion; heedlessness; inconsideration;
carelessness. See <er>Temerity</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Raskolnik</ent>⟦br⟧
